item.description:
New to Voyager? Please start here.
 Using AWS Certificate Manager Voyager can use AWS certificate manager to terminate SSL connections for LoadBalancer type ingress in aws provider. To use this feature, add the following annotations to Ingress;
ingress.appscode.com/annotations-service: |{ &#34;service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-ssl-cert&#34;: &#34;arn:aws:acm:...&#34;,&#34;service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-backend-protocol&#34;: &#34;http&#34;,&#34;service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-ssl-ports&#34;: &#34;443&#34;}Voyager operator will apply these annotation on LoadBalancer service used to expose HAProxy to internet. This service will (logically) listen on port 443, terminate SSL and forward to port 80 on HAProxy pods.
